# How to update the README.md

This guide provides detailed instructions for effective modifications to the [README.md](mdc:README.md) file, following best practices for documentation and collaboration.

---

## Structure

- Title: Project name.
- Purpose: Explain the purpose of the project, what it does, and who it benefits.
- Prerequisites: List everything the user needs before attempting to install the application (e.g., Node.js, Docker, database Y).
- Installation guide: A clear and concise step-by-step guide so that anyone can install and run the project on their own machine.
- Environment variables: List and describe all required environment variables for the application to run properly.
- Features: List all the main features of the project and indicate the relevant screens and pages.
- How to use: Teach the user how to navigate the application and achieve the project's goals. Include instructions, if necessary, on how to configure specific resourcesâ€”for example, how to obtain API keys from service Z.
- Technologies: List the main technologies used to build the project.
- License: Define the usage terms of your code and refer to the LICENSE file in the repository.

---

## Best Practices

- Always write in English.
- Focus on write short paragraphs, like 3 lines maximum.
- Write clear, objective and inclusive language.
- Use markdown correctly for headings, lists, code blocks, links, and images.

---

## Don'ts

- Don't expose senstitive information.
- Don't use informal language or slang.
- Don't include irrelevant or personal information.

